begin_memory_text: nothing much she was very quiet so I was essentially pulling out whatever questions about life I could think of...we did talk about how we were both only children tho.
middle_memory_text: covid? dont really remember the middle I felt like we had an eternity left. we talked about her wedding
end_memory_text: covid more and the world around us.its such a weird time that every conversation seems to end up discussing covid again
rest_of_day_open: pretty boring and lonely. everyone has been flaking even more than usual so it will probably be difficult to actually see friends. I hate staring at a screen all day and dread another week of online classes. the weather is getting colder so there will be less and less to do outside.
critical_positive: we had a time limit. This helped us know that we didn't have to keep trying to find things to talk about forever. I think I am pretty good at coming up with questions and trying to keep the conversation going but I still was pretty low energy and bored
critical_negative: she was  very quiet and we did not have much in common. it is very hard to meet a stranger for the first time on zoom and not have any real interactions to reference. it is especially difficult if one or both parties is not very outgoing. holding the brunt of a zoom conversation is exhausting

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and talked a little bit about where we are from and what we do. We talked a little bit about the pandemic.
middle_memory_text: We talked more about the pandemic and how it has affected us. We talked about my wedding and how it affects her schooling.
end_memory_text: We talked about how the pandemic affected our area and how we want it to end. We said our goodbyes and told each other to have a good day.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will go well. The weekend is coming up and that is my favorite part of the week. I think my fiance and I will have a nice time together. We have some fun things planned so I think that will add to the fun times of the week.
critical_positive: We were able to talk about many different things. It seemed like she was good at coming up with more ideas to talk about. I liked that we were both friendly and appeared to be interested in each others lives. We were able to have a normal conversation even though we were strangers.
critical_negative: I am more on the quiet side so sometimes I get shy talking to others so I think this happened to me. I felt a little awkward talking to a stranger and I'm sure she did too. Sometimes I didn't know how to reply so I just waited for her to talk.
